      <bioghist id="aspace_71e5c2f746b7fbcdfd2ee217ad1ab734">
         <head>Biographical Note</head>
         <p>Gay rights activist and the first openly gay candidate for public office in North
            Carolina, resident of Chapel Hill (Orange Co.), N.C.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_2c0420623f54b11a6294f34622773a95">
         <head>Collection Overview</head>
         <p>Collection contains materials primarily related to the 1984 elections. They include
            correspondence with public officials (among others), articles, and studies. The
            materials reflect Brown's interest and involvement in the Democratic Party, national
            legislation, and issues regarding gay rights.</p>
      </scopecontent>
